{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4d47b65a-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30505"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"30505"},"text":"§ 30505.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Severability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If any provision of this division, an amendment made by this division, or the application of such provision or amendment to any person or circumstance is held to be unconstitutional, the remainder of this division, the amendments made by this division, and the application of the provisions of such to any person or circumstance shall not be affected thereby.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4d47b65b-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/84/dE/s4709"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–84, div. E, § 4709","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2841"},"text":"123 Stat. 2841","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4d47b65c-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4d47b65d-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id4d47b65e-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This division, referred to in text, is division E of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/84"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–84","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2835"},"text":"123 Stat. 2835","children":[],"tail":", known as the Matthew Shepard and James Byrd, Jr. Hate Crimes Prevention Act. For complete classification of division E to the Code, see Short Title of 2009 Act note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s10101"},"text":"section 10101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4d47b65f-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s249"},"text":"section 249 of Title 18","children":[],"tail":", Crimes and Criminal Procedure, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
